Patch Set 1:

Also, FWIW, I'd have merged this patch first and then ask for clarification. This patch is suppose to fix the gate, which should be a priority.

Patch Set 1: Code-Review+2

After discussing this with Flavio, it appears that the change in glance_store was backward-compatible, and glance_store applies the same guarantees as Oslo libraries in that respect. In particular, the main code of Glance (which is the consumer of the library) was unaffected by the change.

What happened here is that the *mock tests* in Glance weren't really forward-compatible due to the nature of mock. This should have been fixed in Glance before the glance_store library was released, but wasn't. This patch catches up and puts everything back in order.
